<p class="">I am asked leave to move the Adjournment of the House, under Standing Order No. 9, <blockquote><q>"to call attention to a matter of urgent, definite public importance, namely, the decision of Her Majesty's Government to proceed with the conference on Central African Federation in the absence of African representatives from Nyasaland and Northern Rhodesia."</q></blockquote> Of course, I have had no notice of this, but the view I have formed is that there will be other opportunities to deal with <span id="408" class="column-number" data-column-number="408"></span> this matter. I think it fails to fall within the Standing Order on the ground of urgency and therefore I decline to accept it.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
