<p class="">I am agreeable to the matter being discussed—[HON. MEMBERS: "Oh!"] Hon. Members opposite seem to be anticipating trouble today, and, by the way they are going on, they will get it. We are quite agreeable to this being discussed through the usual channels, but it is a change of Government policy—[HON. MEMBERS: "No."]—and it should be for the Government to provide the time. I submit to the Prime Minister that he should not be touchy about points of order, because when he was Leader of the Opposition he used to take half an hour or more on fruitless points of order.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
